# Application hotkeys

super-i xfce4-terminal --command tmux
super-o firefox
super-p xfce4-popup-whiskermenu

super-' emacsclient -a "" -c

super-; move-to-next-monitor
        (this is a script and needs xdotool and wmctrl installed)

# Window manager hotkeys

super-j Minimize
super-k Maximize
super-h Quicktile left
super-l Quicktile right

super-y Quicktile top-left
super-u Quicktile top-right
super-n Quicktile bottom-left
super-m Quicktile bottom-right

# Terminal emulator settings

Solarized color scheme
DejaVu Sans Mono Book, 12 point font (17 or 25 on my laptop)

# Misc.

Install xclip to enable tmux to copy to system clipboard.
